SUMMARY:Northwestern University Chamber Orchestra
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T020000Z
UID:53e8286f66b3b09799381c211c3de6b1@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Harvey Felder\, conductor \n\nSchubert’s Overture in C Majo
 r in the Italian Style opens the concert\; the piece was his contribution 
 to the trend of overtures written in the style of the wildly popular Gioac
 chino Rossini. Huang Ruo’s Tipping Point brings listeners to the present
  with a timely symphony tackling the climate crisis. Ralph Vaughan William
 s’s lively The Wasps: Aristophanic Suite closes the evening\, written fo
 r a production of Aristophanes’s satirical ancient Greek play The Wasps.
   \n\nFranz Schubert\, Overture in C Major in the Italian Style\, Op. 170
 \, D. 591 \nHuang Ruo\, Tipping Point \nRalph Vaughan Williams\, The Was
 ps: Aristophanic Suite
LOCATION:Pick-Staiger Concert Hall\, 50 Arts Circle Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-university-cham
 ber-orchestra-8
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-university-jazz-orchestra-8"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Northwestern University Jazz Orchestra
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T020000Z
UID:4474128a870a531925fd614c295028ae@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Derrick Gardner\, conductor\; Ron Blake\, saxophone \n\nThe J
 azz Orchestra welcomes saxophonist and alumnus Ron Blake (‘86) for their
  second winter concert. Previously a member of Roy Hargrove and Art Farmer
 ’s ensembles\, Blake co-founded the 21st Century Band and the Tahmun rec
 ord label with drummer Dion Parson. A member of the Emmy-winning Saturday 
 Night Live Band and the Grammy-winning Christian McBride Big Band\, he has
  appeared on more than 60 recordings as a guest or sideman. His August 202
 5 release\, Ron Blake Scratch Band\, is a reflection on his childhood memo
 ries of local bands from his birthplace of the Virgin Islands. \nRon Blak
 e (arr. Alex Brown)\, RE: Evaluation \nRon Blake (arr. Alex Brown)\, Tom 
 Blake \nRon Blake (arr. Vicky Yang)\, Beyond Yesterday’s Tomorrows \nL
 enny Pickett (arr. Rich Shemaria)\, Kathy \nRon Blake (arr. Lynn Speakman
 )\, Sonic Tonic \nRon Blake (arr. Alex Brown)\, Chasing the Sun \nRon Bl
 ake (arr. Vicky Yang)\, Waltz for Gwen \nCedar Walton (arr. Frank Foster)
 \, Firm Roots
LOCATION:Patrick G. and Shirley W. Ryan Center for the Musical Arts\, 70 A
 rts Circle\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-university-jazz
 -orchestra-8
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
