X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Beth Emet": "https://bethemet.org/event/siddur-prayerbook-hebrew-with-bluma-stoller-3-2/2026-03-16/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:beth_emet
X-SOURCE:Beth Emet
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260316T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260316T120000
DTSTAMP:20260312T212013
CREATED:20251016T010641Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T204302Z
UID:10021482-1773658800-1773662400@bethemet.org
SUMMARY:Siddur (Prayerbook) Hebrew
DESCRIPTION:If you’d like to participate more meaningfully at services\, this class can help you continue to develop your Hebrew skills. Participants will develop Hebrew reading proficiency while exploring the vocabulary\, structure\, and themes of Shabbat worship services and prayers. This class meets a requirement for Adult Kabbalat Mitzvah and is held in Room 202. \nMembers\, click here to register. \nGuests\, click here to register. \nBluma Stoller is a Beth Emet member and a graduate of Columbia University and the Jewish Theological Seminary. She was the North American Director of Academic Affairs for Tel Aviv University and was the recipient of Hillel International’s Exemplar of Excellence Award for her commitment to social justice and tikkun olam. She has held leadership positions in major Jewish organizations\, including Project Otzma and the JCRC of Greater Boston.
URL:https://bethemet.org/event/siddur-prayerbook-hebrew-with-bluma-stoller-3-2/2026-03-16/
CATEGORIES:Adult Programming
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bethemet.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Adult-Hebrew.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Af Northshore": "https://www.meetup.com/afnorthshore/events/312930678/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_af_northshore
X-SOURCE:Meetup Af Northshore
UID:event_312930678@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260313T022014Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260316T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260316T143000
SUMMARY:The Dark Side of the Eiffel Tower
DESCRIPTION:Alliance Française du North Shore\nHolly Clayson will explore little-known\, forgotten and erased aspects of the Eiffel Tower's identity when it first arose in the French capital in 1889. The tallest structure on Earth\, it was the centerpiece of that year's Exposition Universelle. She will discuss the Tower's use of profuse iron ornament and illumination as surveillance alongside a consideration of its function as the emblem par excellence of Republican Imperialism. She will also discuss the imagery of the Tower in the visual arts.\n\nS. Hollis “Holly” Clayson was Professor of Art History at Northwestern University for 35 years and retired in 2020 as Professor Emerita of Art History and Bergen Evans Professor Emerita in the Humanities.\n\n**Program Registration for Members of the AF DuPage: Free**\nIf you're a member of the AF DuPage and are attending a monthly program for the first time\, please RSVP to programmes@AFnorthshore.org with “DuPage” in the subject line. Include your name and Zoom screen name\, if different. If you're a member of our Meetup group\, we'll mark you as such and you'll no longer need to send RSVP emails as long as you RSVP on Meetup.\nIf you're not a member of the AFduNS Meetup group\, you'll need to send an email RSVP for each monthly program.\n\n**Program Registration for Nonmembers: $10**\nIf you're not a member of the AFduNS or the AF DuPage\, the cost of attending this program is $10. [Click here](https://forms.gle/f89WGYhPkj867tYi8) to register and pay online with PayPal by 8 PM the day before the program. There will be no refunds or credits.\n\nWe appreciate reservations by 8 PM the day before the program. Walk-ins may pay at the door on their mobile device.\n\n**Membership in the AFduNS**\nWhile no membership is required for newcomers\, we welcome new members whose membership will support the activities of the AFduNS\, a nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization. For further info\, visit our [website](https://afnorthshore.org/events) or [click here to contact us](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScRxM03DpryO_lZlGWK-aDOCiFHFbivJimTScMOQmWk7KgOJQ/viewform?pli=1). If you wish to join the AFduNS\, you may sign up [online](https://afnorthshore.org/join). Annual dues are $50.00.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/afnorthshore/events/312930678/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260117T171901Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260117T171901Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/7/6/a/600_532290570.jpeg
END:VEVENT
