X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Winnetka Northfield Library": "https://www.wnpld.org/event/abigail-adams-historical-portrayal-leslie-goddard-31151"}
X-SOURCE-ID:winnetka_northfield_library
X-SOURCE:Winnetka Northfield Library
UID:31151
DTSTAMP:20260313T022004Z
SUMMARY:Abigail Adams: A Dramatic Portrayal by Leslie Goddard
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.wnpld.org/event/abigail-adams-historical-portraya
 l-leslie-goddard-31151
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20250701T191339Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260211T161501Z
DESCRIPTION:More than just a wife of 2nd president John Adams and mother of
  6th president John Quincy Adams\, Abigail Adams was a true partner to her
  husband and a committed patriot. In this living-history portrayal by Lesl
 ie Goddard\, Adams recounts her life\, including her famous call to John A
 dams to "remember the Ladies" in the founding of the new nation. She share
 s her opinions of the founding fathers\, displays her lively wit and offer
 s a glimpse at one of the great love stories of all time.
CATEGORIES:Live Performance
DTSTART:20260324T000000Z
DTEND:20260324T013000Z
LOCATION:US
