BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639001"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Clothesline Project Art Making Space | Sexual Assault Action Month
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260402T213000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260402T233000Z
UID:6082f35cd5d9936f379c6bc42577f9e6@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Gather with CSAW to share a message of healing\, resilience\, 
 and hope for survivors of interpersonal violence. T-shirts and art supplie
 s for decoration will be provided.  \n \nThe Clothesline Project is an i
 nteractive exhibit of messages of resilience\, healing\, and hope for indi
 viduals and communities impacted by interpersonal violence and abuse. Thes
 e messages are shared on t-shirts\, which visually represent the statistic
 s of those impacted by violence.  College campuses\, crisis centers\, and
  community organizations throughout the U.S. and around the world have hos
 ted Clothesline Project events since the 1990s to acknowledge the magnitud
 e of the impacts of interpersonal violence.
LOCATION:Foster-Walker Complex\, 1927 Orrington Avenue\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639001
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
