URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/ell-literacy-circle-1584
 9
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251202T222648Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260202T204938Z
DESCRIPTION:Have you ever wanted to be part of a library book discussion gr
 oup\, but you worried that your English language skills were not strong en
 ough?In this class for advanced-level English learners\, we will read and 
 discuss an American novel together\, with the support of Margaret Feit Cla
 rke\, an experienced ESL teacher from the ELL Parent Center. You will st
 rengthen your English skills while learning more about great literature\, 
 American culture\, and the Skokie community. Limited to 16 participants. F
 ree tickets will be given to those who attend.The class will meet on Tuesd
 ays for 12 weeks: March 3-May 12\, 9:30-11:30 am. No class March 31.We’l
 l read and talk about Olive\, Again by Elizabeth Strout. The book offers 
 a series of interconnected stories that provide a portrait of a complicate
 d woman confronting her own mortality.Find Olive\, Again in the library ca
 talog.Find additional titles by Elizabeth Strout in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Discussion,Lifestyle and Leisure,Self-Improvement
DTSTART:20260407T143000Z
DTEND:20260407T163000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Business & Community Center
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
