X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/myths-american-history-fictions-we-learned-and-truth-behind-them-9189"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:9189
DTSTAMP:20260313T021958Z
SUMMARY:Myths in American History
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/myths-american-history-f
 ictions-we-learned-and-truth-behind-them-9189
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251014T010444Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251229T205743Z
DESCRIPTION:All countries tweak their national stories to make the past eas
 ier to explain. But the reality is often far more interesting than the myt
 h. Historian Joyce Haworth will explore a collection of these stories\, fr
 om the light-hearted (was Molly Pitcher a real person?) to the serious (di
 d Lincoln hold enslaved labor?). She will also provide some help in learni
 ng how to detect the fictions within the truth.Keyword: USA 250
CATEGORIES:Civic Engagement
DTSTART:20260409T000000Z
DTEND:20260409T010000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Radmacher Room
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
