X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Evanston Writers": "https://www.meetup.com/evanstonwriters/events/313462483/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_evanston_writers
X-SOURCE:Meetup Evanston Writers
UID:event_313462483@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260313T022015Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260414T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260414T210000
SUMMARY:Screenplay Critique Group
DESCRIPTION:Evanston Writers Workshop\nWelcome to the Evanston Writers Workshop’s **Screenplay Critique Group**. We're a group of professional and aspiring writers who help each other polish their writing through workshop style critique. Writers have the opportunity to receive and give direct\, constructive\, and actionable feedback from attentive readers and writers who understand the craft of screenwriting.\n\n## Details\n\n**\\- This group is for Screenwriters writers\\\, aged 18\\+ at** **INTERMEDIATE to ADVANCED levels only**.\n\n* We will meet monthly on **the second Tuesday of the month\, from 7:00-9:00pm central time on ZOOM**.\n\\- We will critique up to 3 submissions \\(up to 10 pages in Standard Screenplay Format\\) per meeting\\.\n\\- You do not need to be a member to attend or critique\\\, however **you need to be a member in order to submit and have your own work critiqued**.\n\\- This is a GIVE & TAKE group\\. In exchange for giving thoughtful critique on others’ work\\\, you get thoughtful critique for your own\\.\n\\- You must RSVP to each Screenplay Critique Group session in order to receive the submissions we will be critiquing\\.\n\\- If you have a submission to be critiqued:\n\n1. To submit\, please [CLICK HERE](https://form.jotform.com/251125391424147) to upload your submissions or type\nhttps://form.jotform.com/251125391424147 into your browser **by midnight the Friday before critique meeting**.\n2. Put "**Screenplay Critique Group Submission” in the subject header.** (We have many different critique groups and want to make sure it’s directed to the correct folder.)\n3. Include **your email address** and **short** bio (this group is for intermediate and advanced screenplay writers) inside your document so participants know where to send their notes.\n\nEWW is a not-for-profit 501 (C) 3 organization founded in 2007. For more information about Evanston Writers Workshop\, and membership\, visit [evanstonwritersworkshop.org.](http://evanstonwritersworkshop.org./) We have critique groups for all writing levels and genres including for fiction\, memoir/non-fiction\, and poetry that meet in person in Evanston\, IL and also online.\n*Friendly reminder: please send your submissions by the Friday (midnight) before the meeting.*
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/evanstonwriters/events/313462483/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260221T154308Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260221T154308Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/7/b/4/600_530418356.jpeg
END:VEVENT
