BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Winnetka Northfield Library": "https://www.wnpld.org/event/history-billy-joel-35987"}
X-SOURCE-ID:winnetka_northfield_library
X-SOURCE:Winnetka Northfield Library
UID:35987
DTSTAMP:20260313T022004Z
SUMMARY:The History of Billy Joel
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.wnpld.org/event/history-billy-joel-35987
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251113T224002Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260211T161533Z
DESCRIPTION:Though Billy Joel has not released a new rock album in over 27 
 years\, he remains one of the world’s most popular live performers.  Us
 ing performance and interview video clips we’ll trace the arc of Billy
 ’s career from his humble beginnings in Hicksville\, NY to his slow rise
  to fame and his long string of hits including “Just The Way You Are”\
 , ”It’s Still Rock N Roll To Me”\, ”Uptown Girl” and “River Of
  Dreams” to his love life including his marriage to supermodel Christie 
 Brinkley and finally to his current status as one of the world’s most su
 ccessful touring acts.  “If you’re in the mood for a melody…the Pia
 no Man will make you feel alright.”
CATEGORIES:History,Other
DTSTART:20260416T000000Z
DTEND:20260416T010000Z
LOCATION:US
END:VEVENT
