BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/marquis-hill"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Marquis Hill
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260426T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260426T023000Z
UID:57af863d5aa7517c9e8c5ee0eee08502@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:“His genre exchange has the ease of a walk across the street
  to a friend’s place.” \n—Downbeat \nTrumpeter and composer Marqui
 s Hill has made it his mission to break down the barriers between contempo
 rary and classic jazz\, hip-hop\, R&B\, Chicago house\, and neo-soul. The 
 Chicago native and 2014 winner of the Thelonious Monk Institute of Jazz Co
 mpetition has performed as a member of the Chicago Jazz Orchestra\, an in-
 demand sideman\, and a bandleader\, earning accolades with his working ban
 d\, the Blacktet. His collaborations have included such artists as Marcus 
 Miller\, Dee Dee Bridgewater\, Boney James\, Kurt Elling\, Joe Lovano\, an
 d Makaya McCraven. Hill’s latest album\, (Beautifulism) Sweet Surrender\
 , sees its release on March 13.\nThis performance is sponsored in part by 
 WDCB 90.9 FM.
LOCATION:Pick-Staiger Concert Hall\, 50 Arts Circle Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/marquis-hill
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
