X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Morton Grove Library": "https://www.mgpl.org/event/readpool-online-60866"}
X-SOURCE-ID:morton_grove_library
X-SOURCE:Morton Grove Library
UID:60866
DTSTAMP:20260313T022001Z
SUMMARY:Readpool: Salamandre by I.N.J. Culbard (Online)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.mgpl.org/event/readpool-online-60866
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20250806T150358Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T164022Z
DESCRIPTION:Readpool is an adult graphic novel discussion group with a focu
 s on challenging and acclaimed stories.Book Synopsis: Kaspar Salamandre i
 s a bereaved young artist who is sent to stay with his enigmatic grandfath
 er in a land ruled under an oppressive regime\, where there can be only on
 e loved one: The Emperor. In this land where flowers are contraband\, musi
 c is illegal\, and art is created in hiding\, Kaspar discovers a world of 
 art revolutionaries\, espionage and the Secret Police. His search for answ
 ers will bring him face to face with the meaning of sacrifice. But\, will 
 anything bring him closer to overcoming his loss?If you need assistance wi
 th getting a copy of the book\, please contact Nate Miller at nmiller@mgpl
 .org or at 847-929-5115.
CATEGORIES:Books & Authors
CONTACT:Adult and Teen Services\, nmiller@mgpl.org
DTSTART:20260428T000000Z
DTEND:20260428T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Online
IMAGE;ALTREP=salamandre;DISPLAY=FULLSIZE;VALUE=URI:https://www.mgpl.org/sit
 es/default/files/2025-12/A1h7EUnX7fL._AC_UF1000%2C1000_QL80_.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/jazz-small-ensembles-20"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Jazz Small Ensembles: The Music of Miles Davis
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T010000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T023000Z
UID:35991bb1302224129be16bb0b2b9cba5@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Derrick Gardner and Kevin Fort\, conductors\nThe Derrick Gardn
 er and Kevin Fort ensembles continue the celebration of the Miles Davis ce
 ntennial with a selection of the legendary trumpeter\, bandleader\, and co
 mposer’s boundary-pushing compositions. Over the course of a career span
 ning nearly five decades\, Davis remained at the vanguard of multiple styl
 istic developments in jazz\, including bebop\, cool jazz\, hard bop\, moda
 l jazz\, and fusion.
LOCATION:Patrick G. and Shirley W. Ryan Center for the Musical Arts\, 70 A
 rts Circle\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/jazz-small-ensembles-20
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/ell-literacy-circle-15852"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:15852
DTSTAMP:20260313T021959Z
SUMMARY:ELL Literacy Circle
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/ell-literacy-circle-1585
 2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251202T222648Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260202T204938Z
DESCRIPTION:Have you ever wanted to be part of a library book discussion gr
 oup\, but you worried that your English language skills were not strong en
 ough?In this class for advanced-level English learners\, we will read and 
 discuss an American novel together\, with the support of Margaret Feit Cla
 rke\, an experienced ESL teacher from the ELL Parent Center. You will st
 rengthen your English skills while learning more about great literature\, 
 American culture\, and the Skokie community. Limited to 16 participants. F
 ree tickets will be given to those who attend.The class will meet on Tuesd
 ays for 12 weeks: March 3-May 12\, 9:30-11:30 am. No class March 31.We’l
 l read and talk about Olive\, Again by Elizabeth Strout. The book offers 
 a series of interconnected stories that provide a portrait of a complicate
 d woman confronting her own mortality.Find Olive\, Again in the library ca
 talog.Find additional titles by Elizabeth Strout in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Discussion,Lifestyle and Leisure,Self-Improvement
DTSTART:20260428T143000Z
DTEND:20260428T163000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Business & Community Center
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
