BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Oakton College": "https://events.oakton.edu/event/historical-examinations-of-women-in-western-civilizations-in-the-second-world-war-and-beyond-a-virtual-conference"}
X-SOURCE-ID:oakton_college
X-SOURCE:Oakton College
CATEGORIES:Conferences and Meetings
DESCRIPTION:Over two evenings\, this conference explores women's experience
 s in Western Civilizations during and after the Second World War. The exami
 nation will include several countries and situations.\n\n \n\nThe conferenc
 e starts on April 29\, 2026\, at 6 p.m. with introductory remarks by Wendy 
 Adele-Marie\, Ph.D.\, Distinguished Professor of History and Coordinator of
  Jewish Studies at Oakton College.  After each evening session\, there will
  be time for Q&A. Rija Quereshi will deliver the closing statement at the e
 nd of the conference on April 30.\n\n \n\nThe conference proceedings will b
 e published in Adele-Marie’s forthcoming second edition of her OER workbook
 \, History of Women in Western Civilizations. Oakton will also offer the co
 urse Women in Western Civilizations (HIS 236) online and asynchronously in 
 the summer of 2026 to further complement the conference.\n\n \n\nPlease reg
 ister in advance to attend the two-day virtual conference\; the same link s
 erves for both nights. All of the times for the event are in Chicago time. 
 You can check time zones to help you register. Please note that the times o
 f each session are subject to change. For more information about this event
 \, please contact the conference organizer\, Wendy Adele-Marie\, at wadelem
 arie@oakton.edu.\n\n \n\nThis event is sponsored by Jewish Studies and the 
 EGHPS Department at Oakton College. This event is also made possible by a g
 enerous grant from the Oakton Educational Foundation.
DTSTAMP:20260313T022007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260430
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Historical Examinations of Women in Western Civilizations in the Se
 cond World War and Beyond: A Virtual Conference
