DESCRIPTION:This month we'll be discussing Death at La Fenice by Donna Leon
 . "Ladies and gentleman\, I regret to inform you that Maestro Wellauer is
  unable to continue the performance." Someone gave the world’s foremos
 t operatic conductor a dose of cyanide during Intermission. Vice-commissar
 io Guido Brunetti is on the case–but the solution may force him to choos
 e between his duty to the law and his own sense of justice. This is the fi
 rst book in Donna Leon’s beloved series about a detective who is “Vene
 tian to the bone.”Find Death at La Fenice in the library catalog.
