DESCRIPTION:This two-part series invites you to practice ways to have respe
 ctful conversation across differences\, facilitated by library staff using
  the same approaches we use every day at the library. You will build skill
 s in engaging with disagreement in constructive ways. In the first sessio
 n (May 4)\, you’ll learn the tools. In the second session (May 11)\, you
 ’ll build on the skills from the previous session and practice holding c
 onversations. Light refreshments will be provided.
