BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/love-and-information/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Love & Information
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260509T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260509T021500Z
UID:5e609a36a32d2ec4c200d015dbf28d98@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:By Caryl Churchill\nDirected by Claire Bauman \nSomeone sneez
 es. Someone can’t get a signal. Someone won’t answer the door. Someone
  put an elephant on the stairs. Someone’s not ready to talk. Someone is 
 her brother’s mother. Someone hates irrational numbers. Someone told the
  police. Someone got a message from the traffic light. Someone’s never f
 elt like this before.\nIn this fast-moving kaleidoscope\, more than a hund
 red characters try to make sense of what they know.\nApproximate run time:
  1 hour and 45 minutes\, no intermission\nSuggested Ages: 13+
LOCATION:Wirtz Center: Ethel M. Barber Theater\, 30 Arts Circle Drive\, Ev
 anston\, IL
URL:https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/love-and-information/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern University": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/mfa-davids-redhaired-death/"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/mfa-davids-redhaired-death/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:MFA Collaboration Series: David’s Redhaired Death
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260509T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260509T021500Z
UID:e5a9a7e80e59563679b46d4a9a401e21@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:By Sherry Kramer\nDirected by Rosalind Faires \nTwo women
  find that they have everything in common until the death of a brother dri
 ves them apart. Part stand-up comedy\, part stand-up tragedy for two. The 
 redhaired mythology that glorifies and empowers two women leads them into 
 a big love\, but can’t lead them safely out again. A play about the 
 heaviness of the things we carry. \nApproximate run time: 1 hour and 40 m
 inutes\, with one intermission \nSuggested ages: 16+
LOCATION:Wirtz Center: Hal & Martha Hyer Wallis Theater\, 1949 Campus Driv
 e\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/mfa-davids-redhaired-death/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
