X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern University": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/love-and-information/"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/love-and-information/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Love & Information
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260510T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260510T021500Z
UID:8e6235c1e217274ece0c1c19ceab1182@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:By Caryl Churchill\nDirected by Claire Bauman \nSomeone sneez
 es. Someone can’t get a signal. Someone won’t answer the door. Someone
  put an elephant on the stairs. Someone’s not ready to talk. Someone is 
 her brother’s mother. Someone hates irrational numbers. Someone told the
  police. Someone got a message from the traffic light. Someone’s never f
 elt like this before.\nIn this fast-moving kaleidoscope\, more than a hund
 red characters try to make sense of what they know.\nApproximate run time:
  1 hour and 45 minutes\, no intermission\nSuggested Ages: 13+
LOCATION:Wirtz Center: Ethel M. Barber Theater\, 30 Arts Circle Drive\, Ev
 anston\, IL
URL:https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/love-and-information/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern University": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/mfa-davids-redhaired-death/"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/mfa-davids-redhaired-death/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:MFA Collaboration Series: David’s Redhaired Death
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260510T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260510T021500Z
UID:64aa77da15ca541e311711c0977dc3cf@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:By Sherry Kramer\nDirected by Rosalind Faires \nTwo women
  find that they have everything in common until the death of a brother dri
 ves them apart. Part stand-up comedy\, part stand-up tragedy for two. The 
 redhaired mythology that glorifies and empowers two women leads them into 
 a big love\, but can’t lead them safely out again. A play about the 
 heaviness of the things we carry. \nApproximate run time: 1 hour and 40 m
 inutes\, with one intermission \nSuggested ages: 16+
LOCATION:Wirtz Center: Hal & Martha Hyer Wallis Theater\, 1949 Campus Driv
 e\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/mfa-davids-redhaired-death/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/xuefei-yang-guitar"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Xuefei Yang\, guitar
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260510T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260510T023000Z
UID:14efc6684624e79b522a7c3fb61e289d@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Part of the Segovia Classical Guitar Series\n“with sparkle\,
  clarity\, and flair.”\n—New York Sun \nXuefei Yang is acclaimed as o
 ne of the world’s finest classical guitarists. Hailed as a musical pione
 er\, Yang was the first guitarist in China to enter a music conservatory a
 nd become internationally recognized for the instrument. Yang has played i
 n over fifty countries at major venues and festivals\, both in recital and
  with the world’s leading orchestras. Gramophone praised Yang as one of 
 the leading innovators of her generation for continuing to build the guita
 r canon\; she frequently commissions new works\, makes her own arrangement
 s\, and adds Chinese music and chamber music to her repertoire. Yang has p
 layed on over 30 recordings\, with her second album earning “Editor’s 
 Choice” from Gramophone. Her collaborations have included musicians such
  as Ian Bostridge\, the Heath Quartet\, and David Garrett. The UK’s Clas
 sic FM named Yang one of the top 100 classical musicians of our time\, and
  she was awarded a Fellowship of the Royal Academy of Music in 2012. Since
  2015\, Yang has served as artistic director of the Changsha International
  Guitar Festival.  \nSegovia Classical Guitar Series new subscriptions an
 d single tickets are available now.
LOCATION:Patrick G. and Shirley W. Ryan Center for the Musical Arts\, 70 A
 rts Circle\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/xuefei-yang-guitar
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
