UID:25842
DTSTAMP:20260313T021959Z
SUMMARY:Thriving Through Menopause
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/thriving-through-menopau
 se-25842
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260217T164754Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T173032Z
DESCRIPTION:Menopause is a natural transition\, but that doesn’t mean you
  have to suffer through it. Kristin Dold Bennett\, DO\, FACOG\, leads a pr
 actical\, evidence-based conversation about perimenopause and menopause. S
 he'll address hot flashes\, brain fog\, sleep disruption\, libido changes\
 , and treatment options tailored to individual needs. Walk away informed\,
  empowered\, and confident.Dr. Bennett is a board-certified OB-GYN at Mid
 west Center for Women’s HealthCare in Skokie and Buffalo Grove. She prov
 ides comprehensive women’s health care\, including preventive gynecology
 \, annual exams\, contraception counseling\, prenatal care\, and menopause
  management. She is dedicated to personalized\, patient-centered obstetric
  and gynecologic care for women at every stage of life. Learn more at http
 s://mcwhc.com/providers/dr-kristie-dold-bennett-obgyn/Keyword: Health & We
 llness
CATEGORIES:Lifestyle and Leisure
DTSTART:20260511T150000Z
DTEND:20260511T163000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Cosmos Room
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
