BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/own-interview-preparation-reduces-interview-anxiety-22858"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:22858
DTSTAMP:20260313T021959Z
SUMMARY:Own the Interview: Preparation That Reduces Anxiety
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/own-interview-preparatio
 n-reduces-interview-anxiety-22858
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260127T213526Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260309T212010Z
DESCRIPTION:Interviews feel uncertain\, and uncertainty creates anxiety. Th
 is workshop shows how focused preparation reduces both. You’ll build a s
 tory vault of accomplishments to make your value clear\; create confident 
 first lines with powerful\, intentional language\; and sketch a simple 90-
 day plan that signals your readiness. You'll learn to apply powerful\, in
 tentional language so that you start your answers with confidence and how 
 to implement a simple system with a workbook to stay consistent and in co
 ntrol.Presented on Zoom in partnership with the Lake Cook Career Collabora
 tive. The presentation will be recorded and available for viewing afterwar
 d. Register and receive a Zoom link.
DTSTART:20260519T233000Z
DTEND:20260520T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Online
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Morton Grove Library": "https://www.mgpl.org/event/babel-rf-kuang-online-63522"}
X-SOURCE-ID:morton_grove_library
X-SOURCE:Morton Grove Library
UID:63522
DTSTAMP:20260313T022001Z
SUMMARY:Babel-On with R.F. Kuang (Online)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.mgpl.org/event/babel-rf-kuang-online-63522
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251121T180442Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T173808Z
DESCRIPTION:Award-winning\, New York Times bestselling author R.F. Kuang\, 
 creator of The Poppy War trilogy\, Babel\, and Yellowface\, will discuss h
 er genre-bending fiction that blends history\, magic\, and sharp cultural 
 critique.Register hereThis event is made possible by Illinois Libraries Pr
 esent\, a statewide collaboration between public libraries offering high-q
 uality events.
CATEGORIES:Online
CONTACT:Adult Services\, info@mgpl.org\, 8479654220
DTSTART:20260520T000000Z
DTEND:20260520T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Online
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/babel-rf-kuang-24985"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:24985
DTSTAMP:20260313T021959Z
SUMMARY:Babel-On with R.F. Kuang
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/babel-rf-kuang-24985
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260210T224551Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T173109Z
DESCRIPTION:R.F. Kuang’s genre-bending fiction broaches ordinarily seriou
 s topics from a satirical and fantastical perspective. Academic yet approa
 chable\, her work combines history\, magic\, and classical literary tradit
 ion to render powerful critiques of academia\, the publishing industry\, a
 nd even contemporary popular culture. Her most recent novel\, Katabasis\
 , follows two graduate students as they descend into hell after the death 
 of their professor. The screen rights options to the novel were sold to Am
 azon MGM Studios for an upcoming TV series before its publication. Her oth
 er bestselling titles include Yellowface\, Babel\, and The Poppy War t
 rilogy\, and she is the recipient of the Nebula Award for Best Novel\, the
  Goodreads Choice Awards for Best Fiction\, and the American Book Award. 
 Kelly Jensen\, an anti-censorship advocate\, a senior editor at Book Riot\
 , and writer who has compiled such anthologies as Here We Are: Feminism fo
 r the Real World and (Don’t) Call Me Crazy\, will be leading the conver
 sation.This event is made possible by Illinois Libraries Present (ILP)\, a
  statewide collaboration among public libraries offering premier events. I
 LP is funded in part by a grant awarded by the Illinois State Library\, a 
 department of the Office of Secretary of State\, using funds provided by t
 he U.S. Institute of Museum and Library Services\, under the provisions of
  the Library Services and Technology Act. ILP is committed to inclusion a
 nd accessibility. To request accommodations\, please email illinoislibrari
 espresent@ila.org. Register and receive a Zoom link for this event.
CATEGORIES:Books and Authors
DTSTART:20260520T000000Z
DTEND:20260520T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Online
END:VEVENT
