X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:23917
DTSTAMP:20260313T021959Z
SUMMARY:Friday Film
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/friday-film-23917
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260204T004012Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T173113Z
DESCRIPTION:HamnetThis lush\, emotional historical drama—winner of the Go
 lden Globe for Best Drama—is based on the critically acclaimed novel by 
 Maggie O'Farrell\, who cowrote the screenplay with Oscar-winning director 
 Chloé Zhao. Set in 16th-century Tudor England\, the film follows Agnes\,
  a gifted healer\, and her husband Will\, whose marriage is pushed to the 
 breaking point by the sudden death of their 11-year-old son\, Hamnet\, fro
 m the plague. Agnes grapples with a raw grief that threatens to consume he
 r\, while Will ultimately pours his profound sorrow into the creation of h
 is immortal masterpiece\, Hamlet.Starring Jessie Buckley\, Paul Mescal\, 
 Emily Watson\, and Joe Alwyn. Directed by Chloé Zhao. Hamnet received e
 ight Academy Award nominations\, including Best Picture\, Director\, Actre
 ss (Buckley)\, and Adapted Screenplay. 2025 : 126 minutes : Rated PG-13 f
 or thematic content\, some strong sexuality\, and partial nudity : Histori
 cal dramaFree tickets will be given to those who attend.Watch a trailer fo
 r Hamnet.Find Hamnet in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Movie
DTSTART:20260522T183000Z
DTEND:20260522T210000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Petty Auditorium
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
