STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260204T025957Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T173117Z
DESCRIPTION:Elio Eleven-year-old Elio believes that extraterrestrials are 
 out there and feels he’d fit in better with them than with people. One d
 ay\, his dream comes true. He's taken to the Communiverse and mistaken for
  an ambassador from Earth. This fun action-packed cosmic misadventure expl
 ores themes of loneliness\, belonging\, grief\, loss\, family\, acceptance
 \, self-discovery\, and identity. Elio and his space-alien best friend Glo
 rdon are endearing and relatable\, and the animation is bright and imagina
 tive. Featuring the voice talents of Yonas Kibreab\, Remy Edgerly\, Zoe S
 aldana\, Brad Garrett\, Jameela Jamil\, Shirley Henderson\, and Matthias S
 chweighofer. Directed by Madeline Sharafian\, Domee Shi\, and Adrian Molin
 a. This film received an Oscar nomination for Best Animated Feature Film.
  2025 : 98 minutes : Rated PG for some action/peril and thematic elements
  : AnimationFree tickets will be given to all who attend. Watch the trail
 er for Elio.Find Elio in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Movie
