DESCRIPTION:Monarch butterflies play an important role as pollinators\, and
  their populations are in trouble. You can learn about them and teach othe
 rs\, too.Tend our native garden patch\, observe monarch eggs and caterpill
 ars\, and talk with other library patrons about your observations and how 
 we can all support monarchs. Data will be submitted to the Monarch Larva M
 onitoring Project. All participants receive service hours as part of Teen
  Summer Service. Fill out this contact form to be added to our list of int
 erested teen volunteers and be one of the first to know about volunteer op
 portunities.Email the teen team to learn more or to express an interest in
  volunteering. For grade 6-12.
