X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:25760
DTSTAMP:20260313T021959Z
SUMMARY:A Brief History of Skokie
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/brief-history-skokie-257
 60
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260216T224303Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T201439Z
DESCRIPTION:Illinois became a state in 1818\, but even by the beginning of 
 the 1830s\, Chicago\, as the largest non-Indian settlement\, only had abou
 t 150 inhabitants. Learn about the beginnings of Niles Township\, the firs
 t settlers in the area and their relationship to the Native Americans\, an
 d how this place would eventually become Skokie -- with a new Village seal
  and a new Village flag!
CATEGORIES:Civic Engagement
DTSTART:20260623T230000Z
DTEND:20260624T000000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Radmacher Room
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
