X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:24098
DTSTAMP:20260313T021959Z
SUMMARY:Rohingya Music in Exile--Courage\, Faith\, and Love
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/crossing-borders-rohynga
 -concert-24098
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260205T033048Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T201547Z
DESCRIPTION:The Crossing Borders Music String Quartet shares brand-new arra
 ngements of Rohingya music and its stories of courage\, faith\, and love i
 n exile. Developed after a month of field work in the Rohingya refugee cam
 ps of Cox's Bazar\, Bangladesh-- the world's largest--this performance sha
 res the melodies\, hope\, and humanity of Rohingya musicians who are the k
 eepers of their people’s stories and cultural legacy. Transcend physical
  distance with music that helps everyone "see the Rohingya with our hearts
 " and celebrates our shared humanity. Free tickets will be distributed to
  those present at 2:30 pm.
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
